2024-02-06.Rmd
library(tidytuesdayR)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(ggplot2)

Data 

tuesdata <- tt_load('2024-02-06')
#> 
#>  Downloading file 1 of 1: `heritage.csv`
dat <- tuesdata$heritage

Data Dictionary

This was taken directly from the README file in the official tidytuesday site.

heritage.csv

variable class description
country character Country
2004 integer Number of UNESCO World Heritage sites in 2004
2022 integer Number of UNESCO World Heritage sites in 2022

Explore data 

dim(dat)
#> [1] 3 3
glimpse(dat)
#> Rows: 3
#> Columns: 3
#> $ country <chr> "Norway", "Denmark", "Sweden"
#> $ `2004`  <dbl> 5, 4, 13
#> $ `2022`  <dbl> 8, 10, 15
knitr::kable(dat)
country 2004 2022
Norway 5 8
Denmark 4 10
Sweden 13 15

Tidy data 

tidyDat <- dat |> 
    pivot_longer(names_to = "year", values_to = "n", cols = 2:last_col())
knitr::kable(tidyDat)
country year n
Norway 2004 5
Norway 2022 8
Denmark 2004 4
Denmark 2022 10
Sweden 2004 13
Sweden 2022 15

Visualization 

set.seed(3)
(
    p1 <- tidyDat |> 
        ggplot(aes(country, n)) + 
        geom_col(aes(fill = year), color = "black", position = "dodge") +
        labs(
            x = "Country", y = "Number of heritage sites"
        ) +
        scale_fill_manual(
            name = "Year",
            values = unname(palette.colors())[c(3, 4)]
        ) +
        theme_bw()
)
